official_title: A bill relating to the dutiable status of fresh, chilled, or frozen cattle meat and fresh, chilled, or frozen meat of goats, sheep and lambs and beef prepared in air-tight containers and beef prepared whether fresh, chilled or frozen, and lamb or mutton prepared or preserved.

summary.text: Provides, under the Tariff Schedules of the United States, that the following meats shall be duty-free: (1) fresh, chilled, or frozen cattle meat; (2) fresh, chilled, or frozen meat of goats, sheep and lambs; (3) beef prepared in air-tight containers, (4) beef prepared whether fresh, chilled, or frozen; and (5) lamb or mutton prepared or preserved.

titles.title: A bill relating to the dutiable status of fresh, chilled, or frozen cattle meat and fresh, chilled, or frozen meat of goats, sheep and lambs and beef prepared in air-tight containers and beef prepared whether fresh, chilled or frozen, and lamb or mutton prepared or preserved.
